BS, XI, 876-82 (M. Chiara Celletti).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1466">Sergius was one of the most popular saints
          of the Orient. He was a Roman soldier martyred shortly after his friend <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1153">Bacchus</persName> since he refused to sacrifice to
          the Roman gods. Sergius was decapitated at <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/165">Resafa</placeName> on the <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/82">Euphrates</placeName>.</note>
                    <event type="veneration" source="#bib1466-2">
                        <desc>The saint is venerated on 10/7/2014.</desc>
                    </event>
                    <note type="disambiguation">with <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1153">Bacchus</persName>
                    </note>
